Deferred prosecution agreement hearing on July 15, 2024 at 09:30 am.

(Case called at 3:00 PM) Defendant Jessica P Palacio in court. Attorney Andrew Irlbeck appears in court for Defendant Jessica Palicio. District Attorney Peter Rindal appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defense indicates there is an agreement. Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver. State to file Information. Defense recites the joint sentence recommendation. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1- Obtaining a Controlled Substance by Fraud as part of 24 months Deferred Acceptance of a Guilty Plea Agreement and No Contest to Count 2- Prescription Drugs- False or Forged Prescription Order. Court accepts Deferred Acceptance of a Guilty Plea Agreement on Count 1 and withholds finding of guilt. Court accepts plea on Count 2 and finds the Defendant guilty. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in. 
Court orders on Count 2- Defendant to provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge, Court costs.
